      • createACLEntry

        NotesACLEntry createACLEntry(java.lang.String name,
                           int level)
                             throws NotesApiException
        Creates an entry in the ACL with the name and level that you specify.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the person, group, or server for whom you want to create an entry in the ACL. You must supply the complete name, but hierarchical names can be in abbreviated format. Case is not significant.
        level - The level that you want to assign to this person, group, or server in the ACL. May be any of the following: ACL.LEVEL_NOACCESS, ACL.LEVEL_DEPOSITOR, ACL.LEVEL_READER ACL.LEVEL_AUTHOR, ACL.LEVEL_EDITOR, ACL.LEVEL_DESIGNER, ACL.LEVEL_MANAGER
        Returns:
        The newly-created entry.
        Throws:
        NotesApiException
